args: Now, to select a gift for Nefaria...\nGoodness, but this is proving troublesome.
Well, we know we'll at least step over the\nbar set for us by Luca and Ranzal.
We've come up with a lot of ideas,\nbut none of them seem perfect.
Every time we think we've figured out the\nthing she wants, it ends up not feeling\nquite right somehow.
Well, let's consider the one thing Ranzal\nsaid before that DID have some merit.
You mean the bit about finding something\nunusual that even a queen couldn't have?
Yesâ€”though how he came up with beef\nout of that boggles the mind.
Still, the initial reasoning WAS sound.\nWe now need to determine what kind of\nout-of-the-ordinary thing she wants.
I've rolled this over and over in my mind\nand STILL can't come up with anything!
If this were a gift for my darling,\nI'd know exactly what to give him!
Is that so? Well then, if you WERE giving\na gift to His Highness, what would it be?
There's no other gift in the world like me,\nfor I am the one and only!
Oh, come now! Was it really so bad?!
It's perfectly natural for a maiden in love\nto try and give her everything to the object\nof her affecti...
Hm? You look as if you've had an idea.
I have it! I know what Nefaria wants!
She must have been suffering from some\nunrequited loveâ€”for even a queen cannot\nrule over an unwilling suitor's heart.
I suppose I understand your reasoning,\nbut it doesn't exactly mesh with my\nunderstanding of Nefaria's character.
Oh come now! She's a lady, is she not?\nShe must have suffered some degree of\nheartbreak in the days gone by.
I fear there was no such person.
Nefaria?! When did you get here?!
A moment ago. I saw you conversing most\nintently, and thought to come over and see\nwhatever was the matter.
Er, and if I might be so forward, were you\ntruly discussing whether or not I had ever\nsuffered from an unrequited love?
No! I mean, yes! I mean...not exactly.\nWe were actually just wondering about\nwhat kind of gift to get you.
But then we somehow ended up wandering\ninto that other discussion.
Thank you for not being upset.
How can I be upset? The sincerity of your\ndiscussion was plain even from afar.
Thank you. But back to the subject at hand.\nYou're apparently quite vexed over what\nmanner of gift might be appropriate.
However, you should understand that I\nwould be gladdened to receive even the\nsmallest trinket, if only it came from you.
I do not dissemble in this, friends.\nAnything would be acceptable.
Why, just look at the lengths you are going\nto in an attempt to sate my desire!
That alone is enough to make me content.
Now then, I must be off. Saint Starfall\nstill has many gifts to deliver this day.
...Ladies? Were we REALLY trying to make\nNefaria happy?
I was just wondering the same thing.\nPerhaps we were only...
We felt we had to give her something\nperfect because we were so disgusted\nwith Ranzal and Luca's poor attempts.
Let's think carefully one more time and\nREALLY try to make Nefaria happy.
Here, Nefaria. Some light, sturdy shoes.
I heard you liked dancing, and thought\nthese would serve you well in that.
And from me, a new handkerchief.
Please use it during those times when\nthe grime of battle becomes too much.
And this tiny bottle is full of my mana.\nIf you use it, it will create an arid,\ndesert-like environment all around you.
Give it a try if your travels have you\nyearning for the sights of home!
Thank you, one and all. Truly.
Hmm. I can see from the look on your face\nthat we still haven't found the thing you\ndesired in your past.
Prithee, do not concern yourself so.
The strength of your feelings for me come\nthrough in these gifts quite clearly.
They make me truly and deeply happy.
